      <p>If you frequently switch between units, bookmark our <a href="/calculators/health/pace-calculator/">Pace Calculator</a> and let it do the arithmetic for you. One small rounding error in a pace conversion can throw off your race plan by several minutes over a long distance.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Target Pace Tables for Popular Race Distances</h2>
      <p>Knowing your target pace before race day removes guesswork and prevents the most common mistake in distance running: starting too fast. The tables below show what pace you need to hold for common finish times at each standard race distance.</p>

      <h3>5K (3.1 Miles)</h3>
      <p>The 5K is the most popular race distance worldwide. It is short enough that beginners can complete it after just a few weeks of training, yet fast enough that experienced runners find it brutally demanding at race pace.</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Finish Time</th><th>Pace (min/mile)</th><th>Pace (min/km)</th></tr>
        </thead>
